Telegram scenario

The Telegram Message Journey (OSI Model)
The OSI Flow
Layer 7 (Application): You hit "Send." Telegram converts your text into a digital message.
Layer 6 (Presentation): The text is encrypted with AES-256 and RSA (MTProto) and formatted into JSON or a similar data structure.
Layer 5 (Session): The app checks if your secure link to the Telegram server is still active; if not, it re-syncs.
Layer 4 (Transport): The message is chopped into pieces (segments). TCP ensures every piece arrives in order.
Layer 3 (Network): Your phone attaches your IP address and the server's IP address to each packet.
Layer 2 (Data Link): Packets are put into "frames" that carry the physical MAC address of your router.
Layer 1 (Physical): Your phone’s antenna sends the data out as radio waves (Wi-Fi/LTE).
